          Estimated disk space required: &highlight-buildsize;
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Estimated build time: &highlight-time;
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect3">highlight Dependencies</bridgehead>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Required</bridgehead>
    <para role="required">
      <xref linkend="lua"/>, and
      <xref linkend="boost"/>
    </para>


    <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Optional</bridgehead>
    <para role="optional">
      <xref linkend="doxygen"/>, (to build documentation)
      <xref linkend="qt4"/> (to build gui), or
      <xref linkend="qt5"/>
    </para>

    <para condition="html" role="usernotes">
      User Notes: <ulink url="&blfs-wiki;/highlight"/>
    </para>
  </sect2>

  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Installation of highlight</title>

    <para>
      Install <application>highlight</application> by running the following
      command:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>

make
</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      This application does not have a test suite.
    </para>

    <para>
      Now, as the <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem> user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make install</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      If you have QT4 or QT5 installed and want to install the gui as the 
      <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem> user issue the following
      command:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make install-gui</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>

  <sect2 role="commands">
    <title>Command Explanations</title>

    <para>
      <option>make lib-static</option>: This option will 
      compile only the static library.
    </para>

    <para>
      <option>make lib-shared</option>: This option will 
      compile only the shared library.    
    </para>

    <para>
      <option>make gui</option>: This option will
      compile static library and the Qt 4.x or Qt 5.x
      GUI
    </para>

    <para>
      <option>make apidocs</option>: This option will
      build the documentation if <application>doxygen</application>
      is installed.
    </para>    

  </sect2>

